pageContext.claim: “And don't forget, I'm paying interest. I didn't have funny money to play with. President Obama had zero interest. I have interest to pay. And now, a lot of people that weren't getting interest in their money for many years -- you understand -- they're now actually getting interest on their money.”
pageContext.analysis: Obama, of course, faced the worst economic crisis since the Great Depression, with unemployment reaching 10 percent. The economy is now basically at full employment. Zero percent interest rates would mean the economy was again in a free fall — presumably not something Trump wants.
